'''Bertha Pauline Dutton''' (born in [[Algona, Iowa]] on March 29, 1903; died September 11, 1994<ref name="cambridge">{{cite journal|url=https://www.cambridge.org/core/services/aop-cambridge-core/content/view/81D509A307D429D4F9B78961ED6143F2/S0002731600044334a.pdf/div-class-title-bertha-pauline-dutton-1903-1994-div.pdf|year=1997|journal=American Antiquity| volume=62|issue=4|pages=652–658|title=OBITUARY – BERTHA PAULINE DUTTON, 1903–1994 |accessdate=2017-11-20}}</ref>) was an archaeologist and ethnologist specializing in the [[Southwestern United States|American Southwest]] and [[Mesoamerica]]. She became a curator for the [[Museum of New Mexico]] in [[Santa Fe, New Mexico]] in 1936.<ref name="adobegallery">{{cite web|url=https://www.adobegallery.com/books/authors/Bertha_P_Dutton171761112|title=Bertha P. Dutton - Author|website=Adobe Gallery, Santa Fe|accessdate=2017-11-20}}</ref>

